    "body": "### Problem\n\nI needed to reformat a file that included a list of paths to images to json lines that included a the filepath and the label of the data (for a paths.json for a torch model).\n\nI created a macro to do this ~15 keystrokes and then attempted to run it for the whole file by typing ```1500@@```. It has been running for the past hour at 100% CPU utilization, freezing the entire editor with no sign of finishing. \n\nWhy does it take over an hour to preform 1500 repetitions of a 15 keystroke macro?\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n1. Create a file with ~1500 lines.\n2. Create a macro on one of those lines that as its last step moves to the next line via 'j'.\n3. run this macro for the whole file by typing ```@@1500```\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nI would expect this to take no more than 60 seconds and am curious why it takes a hour.\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\n0.11.2\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nVim behaves the same.\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nArch Linux 6.15.5\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nST\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nst-256color\n\n### Installation\n\npacman -S",
